Git History Cheat Sheet

Basic Viewing:

git log: Shows the commit history in reverse chronological order.

Information Displayed (Default):

	• Commit hash (SHA-1)
	• Author (name and email)
	• Date
	• Commit message

Concise Output:

git log --oneline: Displays each commit on a single line with a shortened hash and the commit message.

Graphical View:

git log --graph --all --oneline --decorate: Shows an ASCII graph of the branch and merge history, including all branches, with commits on one line and branch/tag decorations.

Viewing Commit Changes (Diff):

git log -p <commit-hash> or git log --patch <commit-hash>: Shows the detailed changes (diff) introduced by a specific commit.

git show <commit-hash>: Displays information about a commit, including the author, date, message, and the patch.

Filtering by Time:

git log --since="<date>" or git log --after="<date>": Shows commits made after the specified date. Examples:

git log --since="1 week ago"

git log --since="yesterday"

git log --since="2023-10-26"

git log --until="<date>" or git log --before="<date>": Shows commits made before the specified date. Examples:

git log --until="today"

git log --until="2 days ago"

git log --until="2023-11-01"

git log --since="<start_date>" --until="<end_date>": Shows commits within a specific date range.

Filtering by Author:

git log --author="<pattern>": Shows commits whose author matches the specified pattern (can be a name or part of an email). Example:

git log --author="John"

git log --author="jane.doe@"

Filtering by Commit Message:

git log --grep="<pattern>": Shows commits whose message contains the specified pattern. Example:

git log --grep="fix bug"

git log --grep="refactor"

Limiting the Number of Commits:

git log -n <number>: Shows the last <number> of commits. Example:

git log -n 5 (shows the last 5 commits)

Viewing Changes to a Specific File:

git log <file>: Shows the commit history that includes changes to the specified file.

git log -p <file>: Shows the commit history with the diff for the specified file.

Combining Options:

You can combine these options to create more specific history views. For example:

git log --oneline --author="John" --since="last month": Shows a concise list of commits made by "John" in the last month.
